articles.author: KAREL JANICEK
articles.description: PRAGUE (AP) — A lone gunman opened fire Thursday in a university building in downtown Prague, killing at least 15 people and injuring more than 20 in the Czech Republic’s worst mass shooting, police and the city’s rescue service said.
articles.title: A lone gunman opens fire in a Prague university, killing 15 people and injuring 24

articles.author: ALANNA DURKIN RICHER and LINDSAY WHITEHURST
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Donald Trump touts his transformation of the U.S. Supreme Court as one of his presidency's greatest accomplishments.
articles.title: Trump transformed the Supreme Court. Now the justices could decide his political and legal future

articles.author: NAJIB JOBAIN, JACK JEFFERY and COLLEEN BARRY
articles.description: RAFAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — More than half a million people in Gaza — a quarter of the population — are starving, according to a report Thursday by the U.N. and other agencies that highlights the humanitarian crisis caused by Israel's bombardment and siege on the territory in response to Hamas' Oct.
articles.title: UN says more than 1 in 4 people in Gaza are starving because of war

articles.author: MICHAEL R. SISAK and LARRY NEUMEISTER
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Rudy Giuliani filed for bankruptcy on Thursday, acknowledging severe financial strain exacerbated by his pursuit of Donald Trump false 2020 election claims and a jury's award of $148 million to two former Georgia election workers he defamed.
articles.title: Rudy Giuliani files for bankruptcy days after being ordered to pay $148 million in defamation case

articles.author: STEPHEN GROVES, LISA MASCARO and REBECCA SANTANA
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Amid grueling negotiations, the contours of a bipartisan border security and immigration deal are beginning to take shape, emerging even as Congress leaves town having failed to publicly unveil any details of the package that's central to unlocking stalled aid for Ukraine.
articles.title: A deal on US border policy is closer than it seems. Here's how it is shaping up and what's at stake

articles.author: BILL BARROW
articles.description: ATLANTA (AP) — Some top Democrats are worried that a dip in Black voter turnout, along with other challenges, could doom President Joe Biden and his party in 2024.
articles.title: Biden should keep expanding approach to Black voters, group of Democratic strategists says

articles.author: HOLLY RAMER
articles.description: CONCORD, N.H. (AP) — Zach Robinson spent decades trying to fight off nightmares about being raped as a child at New Hampshire’s youth detention center. He died last month, still waiting for accountability for his alleged abusers.
articles.title: Hundreds alleged assault by youth detention workers. Years later, most suspects face no charges

articles.author: ED WHITE, DEL QUENTIN WILBER and MADDY PEEK
articles.description: DETROIT (AP) — The serial killer lured women one by one into vacant homes to be murdered, posing their nude or partially clothed corpses amid cheap booze pints, crumbling sheetrock and hypodermic needles.
articles.title: A serial killer set Detroit on edge. Police missteps over 15 years allowed him to roam free

articles.title: Ready, set, travel: The holiday rush to the airports and highways is underway

articles.author: PATRICK ORSAGOS
articles.description: TROY, Ohio (AP) — Each morning when she wakes up, Juanita Mengel removes the silicone liner of her prosthetic leg out from under a heated blanket so that the metal parts of the artificial limb don't feel as cold on her skin when she straps the pieces together.
articles.title: Cat-owner duo in Ohio shares amputee journey while helping others through animal therapy
